Lithuanian startup "Ocredo" enables small European companies to take advantage of greater business opportunities. By using different open datasets, this company creates a product that makes it easy to understand data and help businesses solve problems (https://bznstart.lt/verslas/startuolis/vilniuje-isikurusi-okredo-pritrauke-650-tukst-euru-uz-atviru-duomenu-platforma/, https://www.facebook.com/OkredoLT/videos/561536649037977/, https://okredo.com/en-lt/open-data-platform). 

1.	Open data not only increases the transparency of the organization and contributes to the improvement of the services provided, but also provides greater opportunities to engage the public, researchers, analysts and organizations by providing access to open data in ways that are convenient for them. The most popular sets of open data of the Bank of Lithuania on the data.gov.lt portal are the following:
-	Address data of ATMs installed in Lithuania, which are collected quarterly from payment service providers operating in Lithuania and independent ATM network managers;
-	balance sheet data of insurance companies, compiled from the data of Lithuanian insurance companies (excluding their branches established in other countries) and the data of branches of insurance companies of other countries established in our country;
-	external sector statistics, including balances of payments and international investments, foreign reserves and foreign debt statistics;
-	statistical data of payments – statistical indicators reflecting the Lithuanian payments market, which are collected quarterly from payment service providers operating in Lithuania, i.e. banks, credit unions, payment institutions, electronic money institutions and branches of foreign payment service providers operating in Lithuania.
(https://www.lb.lt/lt/naujienos/pasauliui-minint-atviru-duomenu-diena-lietuvos-bankas-kviecia-labiau-pasinaudoti-suteikiamomis-galimybemis) 

2.	Neurotechnology's solution (https://www.neurotechnology.com/  or https://data.gov.lt/usecases/examples ) enables the automatic collection of freely available data to draw conclusions about the labour market situation and future needs. The solution provides a comprehensive and systematic forecast of the region's labour market needs, allowing for targeted organisation of local vocational guidance services and the formulation of training and retraining services. The solution requires fewer human and financial resources. Other IT solution - https://dayqanalytics.eu/. The app offers free analysis of more than 40,000. For more than 1.2 million employees, you can analyse the number of employees and salary trends by sector, activity and municipality. Data is analysed visually, quickly and interactively. Based on open data, users can draw insights, compare their company's performance against competitors, and develop the right reward policy. At the same time, transparency is promoted and efficiency is improved.

